How to build CLI gem

1. Plan your gem
2. Start with projject structure
3. Start with entry point - the file run
4. Force that to build the CLI interface
5. stub out the interface
6. start making things real
7. discover objects.
8. program.

Bin
- creat a file in bin with (essential name)
- in bin file make sure it can read ruby by adding on line 1. #!/usr/bin/env ruby       (excutive permission through ./bin/(essential name) for when people run project)
- look into bin directory (cd bin/)
- type in ls -lah ,it will show which has executive permission with executive x 
- to add use chmod +x (essential name)
(essential name)::CLI.new.call


cli.rb -- CLI Controller
#class (essential name)::CLI